    Class and Description
    CMObject
    The general base interface which is implemented by every class which the CoffeeMud ClassLoader (CMClass) handles.
    Contingent
    One step above a basic CMObject is an object that is contingent on its environment.
    Environmental
    The core of most object types in CoffeeMud.
    Modifiable
    A Drinkable object containing its own liquid material type, and liquid capacity management.
    MsgListener
    An object which is permitted to handle game events in CoffeeMud.
    Physical
    Something that exists in the physical world and can be affected by the world
    StatsAffecting
    An interface for classes and objects which may affect mobs, rooms, items, and other Environmental types By altering their stats and state objects using the layer system.
    Tickable
    This interface is implemented by any object which wishes to get periodic thread time from the threads engine.
